 roughly... $160 billion. Now before you start spouting that the USA has more people...Japans population is around 126,500,00 people and the USA is 316,000,000. Even cutting the amount for the USA down to half to nearly equal Japan, we'd still be at 400 million. Now, the world rankings are putting the USA at 17th in the world or &quot;average&quot; as many reports have said, Japan is 4th. I work in education and believe me, the spending is rampant, most school districts are in the red... how is this possible with all the money being thrown at our glorious school systems?! I asked a principle why they got rid of wood shop, auto shop amongst othe work ethic programs in high schools. He said, &quot;We're making professional students of these kids and they're going to hate us for it.&quot; Instead of trying to sing praises of public schools while putting down parents who evily send their kids to private schools, maybe we should pull back the veil that government is hiding behind to reveal the real snake eating it's own tail. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1324" language="en" documentId="2854" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="USAlostitsway" date="Aug 29, 2013 8:08PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="5" thumbsDown="0" origId="2854" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1324"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>